      <td> 
        <div align="left"> 
          <p><font face="Verdana" size="-1"><b>Chapter 2: 
            Trouble in Paradise</b><br></font>
            <font face="Verdana" size="-2">(by <a href="http://www.eqraid.org/stories/members.cgi?action=showprofile&login=Oldsalt">Oldsalt</a> <a href="mailto:jbaines@unity.unity.edu?subject=Interactive Fiction"><img src="graphics/email.gif" border="0" alt="send e-mail"></a> 
, added on February 27, 2001  08:59 PM CT (US))</font></p>
        </div>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <br>
  <table width="90%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">
    <tr> 
      <td> <font face="Verdana" size="-1"> He did not have much time for wistful recollection, for at that moment he was nearly knocked on his arse by a short, cloaked person barreling through behind him.<br><br>"I'm back!" the form roared, throwing back his cloak. "Where is Daigeh?!"<br><br> "I am deeply sorry, Ambrose," Aegirson said in a soft voice, pulling him aside, "but Daigeh has passed away."<br><br> "WHAT?!!" Ambrose screamed, "That cannot be true! Where is she now??"<br><br> "She is in her chamber upstairs, waiting to be interred. The ground is yet a bit cold for a proper burial."<br><br> Ambrose hastens up the staircase, so intent on seeing his lost love he almost forgets to snag a beer from the hands of Albrich as he shoots past.<br><br> Running through the hallway, Ambrose skids to a stop in front of the door of his beloved. His breath coming quickly, he opens the door and steps inside.<br><br> She lays still on the bed, her lifeforce fled from her body. Summoning upon all his magical powers, he incants a spell of ressurrection. <br><br>It had no effect whatsoever.<br><br>"NOOOOOOOOOO!" screams Ambrose in profound shock, "THIS CANNOT BE SO!"<br><br>"Bah, STFU," Temporal calls from the next room. "I'm trying to sleep!"<br><br> As Ambrose pulls up a stool to take one last look at Daigeh; resplendant in her shiny tank top outfit, he decides to try to give her mouth to mouth as a last resort.........<br><br> </font></td>
