        <div align="left"> 
          <p><font face="Verdana" size="-1"><b>Chapter 3: 
            Touble in Paradise part-2</b><br></font>
            <font face="Verdana" size="-2">(by <a href="http://www.eqraid.org/stories/members.cgi?action=showprofile&login=Piergeiron">Piergeiron</a> <a href="mailto:Optionw@pacbell.net?subject=Interactive Fiction"><img src="graphics/email.gif" border="0" alt="send e-mail"></a> 
, added on February 28, 2001  02:25 PM CT (US))</font></p>
        </div>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <br>
  <table width="90%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">
    <tr> 
      <td> <font face="Verdana" size="-1">Piergeiron's heart is filled with emotion.  They had finally accepted him into the Clan as a junior member.  All those days of cleaning the stables had paid off. As he walks down the halls of this great keep he now feels he is finally home. His thoughts are disrupted by a shout...."I'm begging you...anyone...wake that love sick dwarf out of his dreams, I cannot get any sleep!" <br>Piergeiron recognized the voice coming from the room.  It was Temporal.  Piergeiron knocked softly and slowly opened the chamber door to the mighty Enchanters room.  Temporal look up from his bed. "Pier" he shouted, "would you please go over and wake that insane dwarf out of his Daigeh is going to die dream, he is having again!" "I swear the high council will here about this!"  Piergeiron silently nods at the Gnome and walks out quickly heading toward Ambrose's chambers. He hears Temporal's voice still muddering curses at the situation. <br>As Pier rounds a corner he is stunned to see a man walking toward him he has not seen in months....</font></td>
